				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'm a level 22 Bard, and I'm undefeated so far in duels. As of late, I have been very bored of leveling, because I leveled very fast, and I mainly sit around the Arena in Lake Rathe challenging ppl. Yesterday, I beat a level 24 wizard, and that was such a close battle. He had some spell called force strike, that took me down to 1/2 bubble of life after he hit me with the spell like 3 or 4 times. The whole time I was slashing the hell out of him, dual-wielding my Brazen Brass Kilijs (10dmg 35fly   a MUST have for bards until you can get ykesha's or something)<BR>
And I managed to kill him just in time to keep my undefeated status.<BR>
I've decided to bring an enchanter friend over with me, of the same level, and play these magic defense songs using MM battle drums. I resisted the 24 wizard like 2 or 3 times, and my resistance can't be over 40 I don't think, so if a 25 bard with MM drums can get his resistance well over 125, my magic resistance at level 22 should still be fairly high, and I figure if it's high enough to resist like everything they cast, then I will just start letting casters waste their mana, and then I'll beat the shit outta them. Another thing, at level 23, I get snare, and when casters are running to get outta my melee range, they're gonna start finding out they can't move so quick no more. ESPECIALLY druids.<BR>
I've killed one druid and he was a tough sob, I'll have to devise a new strategy for them...<BR>
SK's are tough to, beat one a level above me, Harm Touched me for 230dmg! At that point, you just stay away and recuperate, sheesh.<BR>
If you ever have doubts about being a bard, just remember, You get songs that have the effects of like 2-5 spells all in one song at higher levels, and you are SO loved in a group. EVERY time I join a group, and say I'm a bard, everyone says YAY A BARD! <BR>
So bards are a wonderful class to play, so DON'T play em! I kinda like being one of the only bards groups can find.
				</font>
			</td>

